Package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.base

Class BaseQuest

java.lang.Object
io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.base.BaseQuest
Direct Known Subclasses:
BaseQuestSequential
@SpringBootTest(classes=TestConfig.class, webEnvironment=NONE) @Tag("exclude-from-verify") public class BaseQuest extends Object
Base test class providing foundational test setup and utilities.

This class serves as the base for all test classes, handling global test configurations, logging setup, and utility methods for retrieving stored test data. It ensures consistent test initialization and provides convenience methods for accessing stored test artifacts.

    • hookData

      protected <T> T hookData(Object value, Class<T> clazz)
      Retrieves data that was stored by a test hook (e.g., DbHook or ApiHook).

      This method looks up hook-scoped data using the provided key object and returns it as an instance of the specified class.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the type parameter of the returned data
      Parameters:
      value - the key object under which hook data was stored
      clazz - the expected type of the retrieved data
      Returns:
      the hook-stored data, cast to T
